Before making this change, please ensure that public_headers_must_be_c89
additionally includes the following code:

```
if (argc == 12345678) {
  // call every public API function with dummy arguments
}
```

We have a list of public API functions in the code generator (see
https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/templates/src/ruby/ext/grpc/rb_grpc_imports.generated.c.template),
so we ought to be able to make this extension to the program.

Doing so will ensure that we remain linkable with a C linker regardless of
which API's we pull in.

@nicolasnoble, @mattkwong
Additionally, please talk to Nico & Matt and devise a plan on testing. This
change will move all core tests to be C++ tests, and place additional
pressure on the runtime of our test suites (C tests will be empty, C++
tests will be heavy). I'd hoped that we'd be sufficiently far down the
Bazel path that we'd just be able to write bazel test //test/core/... or
bazel test //test/cpp/..., but that looks unlikely, so I'd request a change
to run_tests.py to ensure that it can distinguish between core and cpp
tests. This *may* involve Makefile changes also.
